CommentBody:
I reviewed the config file for the AIC and the Publish Report and discovered that the customer used the wrong URL to access the AIC. 

I deleted the AIC shortcut and created a new one with the correct URL.

For the Publish Report, I ran the command "netsh http show urlacl" to check the urlacl list, and I discovered that url=http://+:8082/ was not listed among the urlacl list.

I manually added the url=https://+:8082/ to the list and restarted the webserver service.
 
When logging in to AIC, a message appears, "Unable to use the SQL Server Database provided," but this does not prevent the customer from connecting
